For the latest news, visit the SparForte web site.

Objective: Error message improvements

Known Issues

CHANGES SINCE 2.6.3

1. Fix: For constant specifications, when the specification is fulfilled the type of the assigned value is now verified with the type of the constant.  Previously the type was not verified.

2. Fix: command type variables must contain paths to files in a secure directory.
3. Fix: arrays with limited or constant elements cannot be rearranged by sorting, shuffling, rotating, shifting, or flipping.  to_array also will no longer write to limited or constant array elements.

4. Fix: malformed numeric literals like "123_" no longer throw an Ada exception.

5. Fix: Added missing entry for doubly_linked_lists.last to the documentation.

6. Fix: vectors package documentation has several corrections.

7. Fix: vectors.delete calculates the vector index correctly.

8. Fix: vectors.delete no longer allows a count with a cursor because of SparForte's meta data label implementation.

9. New: vectors.no_index, vectors.find_index, vectors.reverse_find_index, vectors.has_element, vectors.assign, vectors.decrement, vectors.increment, vectors.to_index. [positive and negative tests needed]

10. Fix: dynamic_hash_table package documentation correction.

11. Fix: doubly linked lists assemble / disassemble are restricted under pragma ada_95.

12. Enhancement: better error messages for procedure / function mismatches.

13. Enhancement: better error messages for some edge cases like using a generic type as a shell command.

14. Refactor: world package was refactored especially moving the symbol table into a separate file.

15. Fix: documentation corrected for doubly_linked_lists.insert_before.

16. New: enum.pos / enum.val [tests needed].

17. Fix: documentation corrected for calendar.to_julian.

18. New: added type calendar.julian_date.

